{
  "texts": [
    "We use this preliminary evidence to justify our focus in this paper on the macroeconomic impact of global temperature.",
    "Descriptive statistics are presented in Table 1.",
    "In addition to mean, standard deviation, maximum and minimum statistics, we include Pearson correlations.",
    "Economic growth has generally be positive over the entire sample period.",
    "It is important to note that the correlation between country-specific climate risk (it) and GDP growth (y it) is negative and significant, for the entire sample, 1901 to 2020."
  ]
}